  "title": "Teeth",
  "body_html": "<b>Teeth Key Figures</b><br /><ul><li>There are 32 permanent (adult) teeth</li><li>Adult teeth start to erupt from the age of 6</li><li>The third molar usually erupts after 17 years of age</li></ul><br /><b>Anatomy of a tooth</b><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti010b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti010.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><b>Innervation</b><br /><ul><li>Innervation of the teeth is an important factor when considering the use of nerve blocks. </li><li>The upper teeth (maxillary) are innervated by the superior alveolar nerves (anterior and posterior)</li><li>The lower teeth (mandibular) are innervated by the inferior alveolar nerve</li></ul><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti012b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti012.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><b>Local anaesthetic nerve blocks</b><br /><ul><li>Lower teeth often anaesthetised using mandibular block or inferior alveolar nerve block. Local is injected into the pterygomandibular space using landmarks as pictured below. An additional block by infiltrating behind the 3rd molar anaesthetises the long buccal nerve</li><li>Upper teeth often anaesthetised by injecting locally either side of the base tooth.</li></ul><br /><I>image illustrating position of inferior alveolar nerve block</I><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti013b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti013.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>Australian dental journal</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_51\" data-linkid=\"51\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_51\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_51\" data-linkid=\"51\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_51\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/j.1834-7819.2011.01312.x\">Applied anatomy of the pterygomandibular space</a></td></tr></table><br><br><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>Wikipedia</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_50\" data-linkid=\"50\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_50\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_50\" data-linkid=\"50\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_50\" class = \"link_bad_count